race.comment: BIT TIRED ACTUALLY (14) sat handy on debut at York and just missed out on the win, finishing 0.3L off the winner. She'll be better for that effort and natural improvement is expected. Will need some luck from the barrier, but if she gets the breaks then she'll be hard to hold out. BUSY FINGERS (3) gets Pike back in the saddle today following a 3.1L defeat at this track and trip 10 days ago. He's likely to end up in the second half of the field from the draw, but he's trending the right way. Rates well on the latest performance and can make his presence felt. PARISH PRINCE (2) will be ready to go first-up following two trials coming in, winning his latest heat at Belmont. The wide draw is a little niggle, but he has some strong figures from last campaign and he's not to be discounted. JIMMY ANGEL (9) will find this easier than recent races and can put his best foot forward. WHISKERS HARBOUR (1) can be in the finish on recent efforts.
